        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold tracking-tight mb-3 mt-8">Frequently Asked Questions</h2>
        <div class="flex flex-col gap-4 mb-8"><div class="border border-gray-200 rounded-lg p-4"><h3 class="text-sm font-bold mb-2">How often do fire extinguishers need to be inspected in Cincinnati, OH?</h3><p class="text-sm text-gray-600">In Cincinnati, OH, fire extinguishers require monthly visual inspections (performed by building staff), annual professional inspections by a licensed technician, 6-year internal examinations, and 12-year hydrostatic testing per NFPA 10 and the Ohio Fire Code (IFC-based).</p></div><div class="border border-gray-200 rounded-lg p-4"><h3 class="text-sm font-bold mb-2">How much does a fire extinguisher inspection cost in Cincinnati, OH?</h3><p class="text-sm text-gray-600">Annual fire extinguisher inspections in the Cincinnati metro typically cost $15–$38 per unit. 6-year internal examinations run $26–$55 per unit. 12-year hydrostatic testing costs $32–$70 per unit. Volume discounts are available for properties with 20 or more extinguishers.</p></div><div class="border border-gray-200 rounded-lg p-4"><h3 class="text-sm font-bold mb-2">Who can inspect fire extinguishers in Cincinnati, OH?</h3><p class="text-sm text-gray-600">Monthly visual checks can be performed by trained building staff. Annual inspections, 6-year internals, and 12-year hydrostatic tests must be performed by a licensed fire protection technician. Ohio requires fire extinguisher service contractors to hold appropriate credentials under Ohio state law. The Ohio State Fire Marshal's Office (614-752-7126) oversees fire protection contractor licensing statewide. Verify your service provider's Ohio credentials before scheduling annual inspections.</p></div><div class="border border-gray-200 rounded-lg p-4"><h3 class="text-sm font-bold mb-2">What are the penalties for fire extinguisher violations in Cincinnati?</h3><p class="text-sm text-gray-600">The Cincinnati Fire Department issues notices of violation for fire extinguisher deficiencies with correction periods. Uncorrected violations can result in escalating fines. Serious life-safety deficiencies — missing extinguishers, expired tags in high-occupancy areas — face accelerated enforcement timelines.</p></div><div class="border border-gray-200 rounded-lg p-4"><h3 class="text-sm font-bold mb-2">Does Cincinnati require fire extinguishers in all commercial buildings?</h3><p class="text-sm text-gray-600">Yes. The Ohio Fire Code (IFC-based) requires portable fire extinguishers in all commercial, industrial, and multi-family residential buildings in Cincinnati. Type, size, and placement depend on occupancy classification and hazard level as defined by NFPA 10.</p></div></div>

